    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "running-with-the-ionic-cli"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#running-with-the-ionic-cli"
        },
        "Running with the Ionic CLI"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "The Ionic CLI can build, copy, and deploy Ionic apps to iOS simulators and devices with a single command. It can also spin up a development server, like the one used in ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic serve"
      ],
      ", to provide ",
      [
        "stencil-route-link",
        {
          "url": "/docs/reference/glossary#livereload"
        },
        "live-reload"
      ],
      " functionality."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "With live-reload, changes made to the app's source files trigger a rebuild of web assets and the changes are reflected on the simulator or device without having to deploy again."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "blockquote",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "p",
        null,
        [
          "strong",
          null,
          "Warning"
        ],
        ": For iOS devices, the device and the computer need to be on the same Wi-Fi network. An external URL for the dev server is also required so the device can connect to it. Use ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "--external"
        ],
        " (or ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "--host=0.0.0.0"
        ],
        ") to bind to external addresses."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "live-reload-with-capacitor"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#live-reload-with-capacitor"
        },
        "Live-reload with Capacitor"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Capacitor does not yet have a way to build native projects. It relies on Xcode to build and deploy app binaries. However, the Ionic CLI can boot up a live-reload server and configure Capacitor to use it with a single command."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Run the following, then select a target simulator or device and click the play button in Xcode:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "ionic capacitor run ios -l --external"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "live-reload-with-cordova"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#live-reload-with-cordova"
        },
        "Live-reload with Cordova"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Cordova can build and deploy native projects programmatically."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "To boot up a live-reload server, build, and deploy the app, run the following:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "ionic cordova run ios -l --external"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
